	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f102216481455728>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>RE: Quick Thought...</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, May 23rd 10:49 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=13385><span id=Scholar>Neptunis</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>278 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.43]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I'm sorry, I should have know not to post here.&nbsp;&nbsp;You follow the HP=GOD STAT philisophy which I don't subscribe too.  Our lifetaps and other spells make up for our lower HP's.  <br><br>I use the lifetaps, debuffs and FD all to either stay alive with agro or dump agro as needed in a group.  I haven't seen the &quot;Big&quot; raids going in with SK's or Pali's as the Main Tank, but I have seen them down the list to take adds or pick up when the Main dies.  Not every Warrior gets to be a Main Tank, in my Guild there are only 4 or 5 Warriors who main Tank, out of a Guild that has over 100 active accounts (not counting multiple characters on the same account).  So the fact that me as an SK isn't going to be asked to Tank Vindi is no big deal, I get asked to tank for XP groups over some of the Warriors.<br><br>So while we don't have the HP's of a Warrior, the big secret is, THAT ISN'T WHY THEY ARE BETTER TANKS!  Warriors are the only ones who Tank Vindi because they have both Defensive Discipline and Auto-Rippost Discipline.  These 2 disciplines are what make them better tanks.  So if you want to really be a Tank, ask for Defensive Discipline, not more HPs.  Give up the Leech Curse Discipline that most of you don't like and ask to get Defensive instead.  That's the ONLY WAY you will ever be asked to Tank Vindi or any of the other big guys.<br><br>The Warriors only goal in life is to be the Meat Shield of these big Raids, I have other skills that I enjoy exploring instead.  <br><br>And yes it is the careful use of lifetaps (all of them) that will keep you alive as a Main Tank when a heal is late or interupted.  We should all know by now that a Cleric heals more with a Complete Heal on a Warrior than they do on CHealing an SK, but that really doesn't matter as they can also get more use out of Celestial Cleansing with us, AND can med during the fight easier as we have better agro control.  Also they save alot of mana spot healing the rest of the group if we are tanking.  So yes a well played SK can tank just not Vindi.<br><br>But again, I'm sorry I even posted here knowing how different our views of the SK Class and HP's are.<br><br>Neptunis</p>&nbsp;<br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 62 DE Gravelord<br>Have Axe, will travel</td></td></tr>
